  "workflows": [
    {
      "id": "daily-standup",
      "name": "Daily Standup",
      "description": "Morning sync for team coordination",
      "schedule": "0 9 * * 1-5",
      "enabled": false,
      "executionMode": "automated",
      "targeting": {
        "communities": [],
        "groups": ["All Hands"],
        "tags": [],
        "agents": []
      },
      "content": "# Daily Standup Workflow\n\nPlease provide your standup update covering:\n\n### 1. Yesterday's Accomplishments\n- What did you complete yesterday?\n\n### 2. Today's Plans  \n- What are your top priorities for today?\n\n### 3. Blockers\n- Are you blocked on anything?\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "weekly-status-report",
      "name": "Weekly Status Report",
      "description": "Weekly progress summary for leadership",
      "schedule": "0 17 * * 5",
      "enabled": false,
      "executionMode": "automated",
      "targeting": {
        "communities": [],
        "groups": ["All Hands"],
        "tags": [],
        "agents": []
      },
      "content": "# Weekly Status Report\n\nPlease provide your weekly status:\n\n### 1. Key Accomplishments This Week\n- Major wins and completed work\n\n### 2. Next Week's Priorities\n- Planned focus areas\n\n### 3. Risks & Concerns\n- Potential issues or blockers\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "github-triage",
      "name": "GitHub Issue Triage",
      "description": "Product Manager reviews and prioritizes GitHub issues for the day",
      "schedule": "0 10 * * 1-5",
      "enabled": false,
      "executionMode": "automated",
      "targeting": {
        "communities": [],
        "groups": [],
        "tags": [],
        "agents": ["product-manager"]
      },
      "content": "# GitHub Issue Triage\n\n**Your Task**: Review the GitHub repository and triage new or unassigned issues.\n\n## Steps:\n1. **Review New Issues**: Check for any new issues filed in the last 24 hours\n2. **Prioritize**: Label issues as P0 (critical), P1 (high), P2 (medium), or P3 (low)\n3. **Assign**: Assign high-priority issues to appropriate engineers\n4. **Report**: Post a summary to the Product & Engineering group with:\n   - Number of new issues reviewed\n   - Critical issues (P0/P1) requiring immediate attention\n   - Recommended daily priorities for the engineering team\n\n## Output\nPost your triage summary to the **Product & Engineering** group so the team knows today's priorities.\n"
    }
  ]
